div1.p:
Did any body else go back with him? - Yes;
Benjamin Harley
and his brother begged very hard of Gypsey George not to beat him any more.

I am servant to Mr. Stratton, at Hackney;
George Turner
is Mr. Stratton's Coachman; the things mentioned in the indictment (repeating them) were taken out of the lodging-room over the coach-house; I saw the prisoner jump down from the window, I pursued him, and took him, he threw the bundle out of his hand; he had the pistol in his hand when I took him: I have had the care of the things ever since.

How long was this before she died? - It was the 16th of April that happened;
Ann Durose
found it under her bed; he parried off the blow of the broomstick with his stick.
